# ERP UI standard (all sections)

Every authenticated module page is wrapped automatically in `index.php`:

```html
<main class="col-main erp-layout">
  <div class="erp-page module-shell">…module output…</div>
</main>
```

`assets/css/erp-module.css` loads for **all logged-in users** via `erp_ui_enqueue()` in `includes/header.php`.

## Rules for new or changed modules

1. **Do not** add per-page layout CSS files unless the screen has unique widgets (register attendance grid, HR command center grid). Register extras in `erp_ui_extra_stylesheets()` in `includes/erp_ui.php`.
2. **Do not** remove the auto wrapper in `index.php`.
3. Use shared patterns:
   - Page header: `erp_ui_page_head(['title' => '…', 'subtitle' => '…', 'actions_html' => '…'])` or `<header class="erp-page__top">` + `<h1 class="erp-page__title">Title<span>Subtitle</span></h1>`
   - KPI row: `<div class="row g-3">` with `<div class="card kpi-card">` columns
   - Filters: `<form class="row g-2 mb-3">` (styled as toolbar automatically)
   - Tables: Bootstrap `.table` inside `.table-responsive` (navy header from ERP CSS)
   - Panels: `.card` with `.card-header` for sections
4. Put layout/styling changes in **`assets/css/erp-module.css` only** — not scattered in `style.css` or new module CSS files.
5. Legacy class `.hr-page` is an alias of `.erp-page`; prefer `.erp-page` in new code.
6. Flash messages: use session flash; `index.php` renders them with `.erp-page__flash`.

## Optional page-specific CSS

Only add a new CSS file when the page has non-standard UI (charts, calendar grid, payslip print). Add the route → file mapping in `erp_ui_extra_stylesheets()`.
